translated: Kihlström, Gustaf Einar, school adjutant, Motala, born on February 17, 1900 in Stockholm to chief accountant Oskar K. and Axelina Natalia Andersson. Married in 1942 to the theological and philosophical candidate, former school adjutant Ruth Siwerson. •— Completed student examination in natural science in Stockholm in 1919, received a degree in philosophy from Uppsala University in 1928, completed a probationary year in 1932. Was a student at Stockholm City Library from 1928-1929, substitute subject teacher in Stockholm's northern commune of Melianskolan in 1929, substitute lecturer in Nyköping privately in 1929, substitute subject teacher in Saltsjöbaden in 1930, in Västanfors from 1930-1931, became a regular teacher in Arvika in 1931, in Karlshamn in 1933, in Kristinehamn from 1933-1937, and has been an adjunct professor of the Swedish language and history with social studies at Motala Public High School since 1937.
